article.headline: Sam Houston St. 62, Texas-San Antonio 59
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- Gilberto Clavell scored 26 points and Sam Houston State edged UTSA 62-59 in the Southland opener for both Saturday night. Clavell added a game-high nine rebounds and was the only player for the Bearkats (8-6) to score in double figures. Jeromie Hill had 17 points to lead the Roadrunners (6-7), who lost their fifth straight. After Sam Houston State's Josten Crow hit a 3-pointer to tie it at 58 with 1:52 to play, Clavell added two free throws to give the Bearkats the lead. UTSA's Stephen Franklin then made his first foul shot but missed the second. Sam Houston State increased its lead to 62-59 with two free throws from Marcus Williams with 9 seconds remaining before Melvin Johnson III missed a 24-foot heave at the buzzer.
